
## 🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we use **Terraform** to provision an **Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC)**, creating an isolated virtual network within AWS. Rather than manually configuring networking through the AWS Management Console, 
we define the infrastructure in code, ensuring it is repeatable, version-controlled, and scalable.

A VPC is the **foundation of almost every AWS architecture**, providing the network environment where cloud resources such as EC2 instances, databases, and load balancers operate.

